notesStmt.note: Censored by Domenico Irosolimitano, Italian censor (active in the last quarter of the 16th and first quarter of the 17th century): inscribed with his name, 1592 (folio 106r); see 61, and appendix § 62-74.
Manuscript description based on Margoliouth, G.: Catalogue of the Hebrew and Samaritan Manuscripts in the British Museum, London 1965.

layoutDesc.layout: Columns: 1; ruled lines: 33 38; written lines: 33 38; Uniform layout. Pricking and hard-point ruling visible. Has some marginal notes. Folio 1r is a paper title page.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: French Ashkenazi semi-cursive of the 14th century.

binding.p: BM/BL in-house. Spine title: 'Tosaphoth Chullin. Hebrew. Brit. Mus. Additional 27,295.'

history.provenance: Acquisition: Samuel Schönblum: purchased from him by the British Museum on 4 April 1866: inscribed, folio fse002v [108v].
